<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01857</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO REINFORCE THE PROHIBITION AGAINST LABOR-ONLY CONTRACTING, AMENDING FOR THIS PURPOSE PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, ALSO KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES, AS AMENDED</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Makes it unlawful for employers to require contractual employees from discharging functions that are currently being performed by regular employees and outlawing the “5-5-5” labor contract, a labor scheme whereby a contractual employee is hired and fired every five (5) months by the employers.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ARAGONES, SOL</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-07-25</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Welfare</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-05-29)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-05-29)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06908</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2016-08-02</td></tr></table>